{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase sentencing for coercive control to 10 years minimum",
        "additional_details": "We feel that current sentencing does not adequately reflect the serious harm caused by coercive control. It involves ongoing emotional and psychological abuse. Victims suffer long-lasting effects on their mental health, self-esteem, and overall well-being, with some facing lifelong trauma or even premature death. We think stricter sentences would clearly indicate that this harmful behaviour is unacceptable and bring justice to the victims and families affected by coercive control.",
        "background": "We want the government to set a minimum sentence of 10 years for coercive control offences. Coercive control is a deeply damaging violation of personal autonomy that causes significant and lasting psychological harm to victims. ",
